text.tspan: CO₂ reductions needed to keep global temperature rise below 2°C
Annual emissions of carbon dioxide under various mitigation scenarios to keep global average temperature rise below
2°C. Scenarios are based on the CO₂ reductions necessary if mitigation had started – with global emissions peaking
and quickly reducing – in the given year.
Data source: Robbie Andrews (2019); based on Global Carbon Project & IPPC SR15
Note: Carbon budgets are based on a >66% chance of staying below 2°C from the IPCC's SR15 Report.
